  "body": "When I fork a prop like this\r\n\r\n```\r\nclass NewOrderContainer extends Component {\r\n  constructor(props) {\r\n    super(props);\r\n    this.state = {\r\n      orderForm: props.orderForm,\r\n    };\r\n  }\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nand then proceed to update state such as this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nthis.setState((previousState) => {\r\n\tconst updatedOrderForm = previousState.orderForm;\r\n\tupdatedOrderForm.quantity = 4\r\n\t\treturn {\r\n\t\torderForm: updatedOrderForm \r\n\t}\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nit mutates the original prop (or more specifically, the state of the component passing the prop orderForm). Mutations to state forked from a prop should be isolated\r\n  ",
